div1.p: United States District Court Western District of Washington Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Antonio Bisegna, alias Disegna, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. } No.2679.
Order for the Withdrawl of the Transcript of the Bureau of Immigration.
Upon the oral motion of the United States Attorney;

It is Hereby Ordered, That the government may permanently withdraw the "Bureau of Immigration Transcript" filed by the government on Feburary 20, 1914, as a part of the government's return to the writ of habeas corpus in the above entitled matter.
Recieved the above named "Bureau of Immigration Transcript" this 28th day of March, 1914.
In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington 50B-4-4
In the Matter of the Application of Antonio Bisegna, alias Disegna for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Order for Withdrawl of Transcript of Bureau of Immigration.
2x Filed in the U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington, Northern Division, Mar 27 1914 Frank L Crosby, Clerk, By EML Deputy.
